## 2026-01-01 - Initial Creation

**RED Phase Documentation:**

Without this skill, Claude Code fails in three ways when asked to design TypeScript applications with clean architecture:

1. **Creates monolithic, tightly-coupled code** - No separation between business logic and infrastructure, everything mixed together
2. **Doesn't understand ports/adapters pattern** - Doesn't know how to create interfaces (ports) and separate implementations (adapters)
3. **Creates untestable architecture** - Direct dependencies on databases, APIs, making unit testing impossible without real services

**Example failure (without skill):**
```typescript
// Claude creates this (BAD):
class UserService {
  constructor(private db: PostgresClient) {}  // Direct dependency on concrete DB
  async createUser(data) {
    const result = await this.db.query('INSERT INTO...');  // Business logic mixed with DB
    await sendEmail(data.email);  // Direct external API call
  }
}
```

**What we need (with skill):**
```typescript
// Hexagonal architecture (GOOD):
interface UserRepository { save(user: User): Promise<void>; }

class UserService {
  constructor(private repo: UserRepository) {}  // Depends on interface
  async createUser(data) {
    const user = new User(data);
    await this.repo.save(user);  // Business logic isolated
  }
}
```

